Patch</span><hr size=1>  Patch 9-4-2002<br>
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
 September 4, 2002 3:00 am <br>
------------------------------ <br>
<br>
- We have rebalanced the rewards for killing NPCs for characters over level 50. NPCs that are considerably weaker than you will give you less experience. NPCs give more experience the higher level they are, and for the best results you should fight the most challenging monsters you can reasonably manage.  <br>
<br>
------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
This single part of yesterday's patch is threatening to ruin part of the game for me.  My main is a 51st level wizard.  I don't know why I chose a wizard as my main....I guess I liked the idea of having a character that could deal lots of damage in a short amount of time.  I found myself enjoying the role I had in a group:  deciding when to open up on the gas and making a mob die quicker was a good role to me.  <br>
<br>
However, my feelings got hurt as I got into the 20s and moved to LOIL.  It was then that I realized that wizards weren't a very desired class in a group.  True, there were classes that had it worse off, like necro's and to an extent mages, but there were numerous times when it would be me and about 3 others LFG, and I would often find that other classes were quick to get picked, while I often had to spend an extra 15 minutes or so waiting for an invite.  I quickly noticed that groups would shout for what they wanted:  clerics, sowers, tanks, chanters....never heard them call for nukers though.  The fact was that a halfway twinked melee could outdamage me over time easily in the 20s.  I lived with that all the way til the mid 30s.  It was then that I realized that Bonds of Force, the wizard snare, could allow me to solo.<br>
<br>
Snare allowed me to not be forced to group.  It quickly became one of my most valuable spells.  Whenever groups didn't want me, it didn't bother me.  I could find something else to do.  I could kite mobs, medd and still LFG.  Not a bad trade off, no one really wanted my wizard, but I could still play the game.  <br>
<br>
Let me make one thing straight at this point:  I prefer to group.  I like to talk to other players while I'm playing.  And I enjoy the different play styles of different classes and the different combinations of classes that are capable of coming together and succedding never ceases to amaze me.<br>
<br>
I probably grouped about 75% of the time that I took to get to level 51.  Now...for some freak reason....Verant has decided that they don't want anyone to be able to get XP for lower dark blue and light blue mobs.  Essentially, they are making any XP that you get soloing worth about half of what it used to be.  I guess that they want to try to force people to group.  Well, Verant, that's well and good, but do you really think groups are going to feel sorry for the classes that are less desired in groups and give them invites? <br>
<br>
Why is my option to solo being eliminated?  Furthermore, with all the level 60 characters that are already in the game, why would you do anything to make it harder for newer character to reach this pinnacle?<br>
<br>
*Casts Protection from Flame, Flameshield and gets ready to hear a bunch of negative garbage*<br>
